The CWGC entry also has this:
&quot;Additional Information:
Son of John and Margaret Wynne Gregg, of 10, Deramore Park South, Belfast.&quot;

And his probate record states:
&quot;Gregg William Henry of 3 Chichester Gardens Antrim Road Belfast 2nd lieutenant 5th battalion Royal Irish Rifles died on or about 1 July 1916 in France on active service. Administration Belfast to John Gregg merchant.
Effects £959 0s 1d in England. Sealed London 22 December&quot;
